WEBVTT

00:09.500 --> 00:11.160
Niles, listen, when Claire gets here,

00:11.335 --> 00:12.878
can you give us
a moment of privacy?

00:13.046 --> 00:14.920
- Of course.
- l'm planning on asking her

00:15.090 --> 00:16.714
to go to Belize with me
next weekend.

00:16.883 --> 00:20.419
Oh! Belize-imo.

00:20.596 --> 00:23.965
You'd better Belize it.

00:25.309 --> 00:27.219
Let's see what we can do
with Ecuador.

00:27.395 --> 00:30.231
- Maybe later.
- Wait, next weekend?

00:30.399 --> 00:32.058
That's awfully soon.
l hope Claire's free.

00:32.234 --> 00:35.069
Lana told me on the q.t. that Claire's
already gotten wind of the trip

00:35.237 --> 00:37.859
and she's eager to go,
so all that's left is for me to ask her

00:38.032 --> 00:39.575
- and act surprised when she says yes.
- Wow.

00:39.742 --> 00:41.403
So are you jealous?

00:41.578 --> 00:45.528
l might be jealous, but as it happens,
l have plans next weekend myself.

00:45.708 --> 00:48.495
You know, Daphne and l are
celebrating one year of being together.

00:48.669 --> 00:52.502
Niles, that's wonderful. Gosh.
So, what do you have in store?

00:52.674 --> 00:54.880
- A weekend alone at my apartment.
- Uh-huh.

00:55.051 --> 00:57.091
See, we don't need
beaches or sunsets.

00:57.262 --> 01:00.548
Just a simple Victorian bathtub
filled with champagne,

01:00.724 --> 01:04.058
us and a non-slip mat.

01:06.356 --> 01:09.274
- Romantic yet prudent. Very good.
- Thank you. Thank you.

01:09.443 --> 01:12.314
Here's where l'm taking Claire.
Do you think she'll like it?

01:13.405 --> 01:16.360
Lush grounds, white,
sandy beaches.

01:16.534 --> 01:19.452
This hotel looks amazing.
She's going to love it.

01:19.621 --> 01:22.705
Niles, l also took the liberty
of buying myself

01:22.874 --> 01:25.366
a new piece of luggage by Mauricio.
Would you care to see it?

01:25.544 --> 01:29.494
NlLES: Mauricio? Try and
stop me. l'm green with envy.

01:34.638 --> 01:35.752
Oh!

01:37.266 --> 01:38.594
[DOORBELL RlNGS]

01:45.400 --> 01:48.567
DAPHNE: Oh, hello, Claire.
- Hi, Daphne.

01:48.737 --> 01:51.109
You seem so happy. What? Why?

01:51.281 --> 01:53.689
Well, it seems
Niles is gonna surprise me

01:53.868 --> 01:56.240
with an exotic trip
for our anniversary.

01:56.412 --> 01:57.610
How funny.

01:57.789 --> 01:59.912
- You know, Frasier--
DAPHNE: l'm so excited.

02:00.083 --> 02:02.076
We've only recently
started going away together.

02:02.252 --> 02:05.170
We wanted to wait until
we got to know each other better.

02:05.339 --> 02:06.418
- Really?
DAPHNE: Yeah, l know.

02:06.590 --> 02:07.670
lt sounds old-fashioned,

02:07.842 --> 02:11.128
but there's nothing worse
for a relationship than moving too fast.

02:12.055 --> 02:13.300
FRASlER: Hi, Claire.
- Hello.

02:13.473 --> 02:14.849
CLAlRE:
Hi.

02:15.017 --> 02:17.590
l've just been telling Claire
about our anniversary plans.

02:17.770 --> 02:22.349
Oh, yes. There's no place like home.

02:22.525 --> 02:24.185
Right. Home.

02:24.360 --> 02:26.234
[CHUCKLlNG]

02:28.448 --> 02:30.240
Claire, listen.

02:30.409 --> 02:32.449
l know this is coming
out of the blue,

02:32.620 --> 02:36.072
but how would you like to go away
with me next weekend to Belize?

02:36.249 --> 02:39.286
- lt sounds wonderful, Frasier.
- l thought you might say that.

02:39.461 --> 02:41.003
Only...

02:41.588 --> 02:45.207
Do you think maybe it's too soon
for us to go away together?

02:46.510 --> 02:49.796
l don't know. Do you?

02:50.598 --> 02:52.638
l don't know.

02:54.311 --> 02:56.636
Well, l'd hate for us to go away
before we're ready.

02:56.814 --> 02:59.519
So are you saying we're not ready?

03:01.986 --> 03:04.608
l don't know. Are you?

03:06.825 --> 03:08.818
l don't know.

03:09.662 --> 03:12.532
l just don't wanna
jeopardise our relationship.

03:12.707 --> 03:13.786
Would we be?

03:14.917 --> 03:17.207
l don't know.

03:18.129 --> 03:23.753
Well, if we don't know,
maybe we should wait.

03:23.928 --> 03:26.134
Okay. You know best.

03:28.308 --> 03:30.051
- So, Niles.
-Mm-hm.

03:30.226 --> 03:32.469
- About our anniversary weekend.
- Mm-hm.

03:32.646 --> 03:34.389
l'm trying to figure out what to bring.

03:35.232 --> 03:41.069
Will your apartment be warm
that weekend or unseasonably cold?

03:42.365 --> 03:45.450
Well, l keep the thermostat
at a steady 7 1 ,

03:45.619 --> 03:48.288
but l'm flexible
within a degree or two.

03:48.455 --> 03:49.831
[CHUCKLlNG]

03:52.126 --> 03:53.241
Will we snorkel?

03:59.718 --> 04:04.131
Well, Daphne,
you're making me blush.

04:04.307 --> 04:07.142
Oh, Niles, stop it.
l know about the trip to Belize.

04:07.310 --> 04:10.097
l'm sorry. l overheard you
talking to your brother.

04:10.272 --> 04:13.143
Trust you to plan
something so romantic.

04:13.317 --> 04:15.986
- Oh, that isn't--
- Oh, stop the charade.

04:16.153 --> 04:18.063
A bathtub full of champagne.
Please.

04:18.238 --> 04:21.074
We used to do that in high school.

04:25.455 --> 04:29.501
Well, turns out
l'm not going to Belize after all.

04:29.668 --> 04:33.252
Claire thinks it may be too soon
for us to go away together.

04:33.423 --> 04:35.462
Or l do.

04:35.634 --> 04:37.840
l forget who spoke last.

04:38.971 --> 04:40.762
Well, l'm so sorry.
You must be devastated.

04:40.931 --> 04:42.260
Well...

04:42.433 --> 04:44.971
Can l have your reservations?

04:45.144 --> 04:46.259
Excuse me?

04:46.437 --> 04:49.723
Well, l've decided to go away
with Daphne for our anniversary.

04:51.360 --> 04:52.439
Why not?

04:52.611 --> 04:55.281
At least one of us should have
the most romantic week of his life.

04:55.448 --> 04:57.405
Thank you, Frasier.
l only wish it could be you.

04:57.575 --> 04:59.782
You suppose
l could borrow your new luggage?

04:59.953 --> 05:01.945
- That's too far.
- Mm-hm.

05:04.833 --> 05:06.328
Well, it's official.

05:06.502 --> 05:09.171
Niles is whisking me away
next weekend.

05:09.338 --> 05:12.624
l'm so excited.
Each trip just gets better and better.

05:12.800 --> 05:15.921
- Because you waited.
- l suppose.

05:16.096 --> 05:20.675
Looking back, l can't believe we held
off for so long. All the fun we missed.

05:20.851 --> 05:25.348
Let's face it, when it's the right person,
there's no sense in waiting.

05:26.900 --> 05:28.857
Well, here we are, Claire.

05:29.027 --> 05:30.605
- Thank you.
- Yes.

05:30.779 --> 05:34.113
- Frasier, about Belize--
- Now, now, Claire.

05:34.283 --> 05:36.525
We've made our decision,
and l think it's a good one.

05:36.702 --> 05:39.110
Maybe it's not too soon to go away.

05:39.289 --> 05:40.783
Go on.

05:41.291 --> 05:44.577
Are we possibly denying ourselves
a wonderful trip?

05:44.753 --> 05:48.253
Well, examining it from all angles,
one could certainly make a case--

05:48.424 --> 05:51.710
- Let's go!
- l'm already packed.

05:51.886 --> 05:53.844
- l'd better run.
- Right. Right.

05:54.014 --> 05:55.342
l thought we were having lunch.

05:55.515 --> 05:57.804
lf we're going to Belize,
l've got some shopping to do.

05:57.976 --> 05:59.471
FRASlER:
What do you mean if?

05:59.645 --> 06:01.305
What do you mean?

06:01.480 --> 06:02.595
- Just go shop.
- Ah!

06:03.649 --> 06:05.025
- Bye.
FRASlER: Bye-bye.

06:05.485 --> 06:06.600
Niles, l'm sorry.

06:06.778 --> 06:09.067
lt turns out Claire and l
are going to Belize after all.

06:09.239 --> 06:11.612
You and Daphne
will have to go someplace else.

06:11.784 --> 06:14.073
Wait. Daphne has her heart
set on Belize.

06:14.245 --> 06:18.160
This is not ''Cranes Go Caribbean.''
l wanna be alone with Claire.

06:19.376 --> 06:20.751
- Hey, guys.
FRASlER: Oh, hi, Dad.

06:20.919 --> 06:26.424
Hey, guys. Ariel, come and say hello
to Frasier and Niles.

06:26.592 --> 06:28.336
- Say hello.
- Hello.

06:28.511 --> 06:30.053
- Say hello.
- Hello.

06:30.221 --> 06:33.721
- Say hello.
- lt's all right, Roz. That's enough.

06:33.892 --> 06:36.679
Ariel just joined
Martin's dog group at the park.

06:36.854 --> 06:40.188
- Eddie was his sponsor.
- Oh, well...

06:40.358 --> 06:43.228
And Ariel discovered squirrels.

06:43.403 --> 06:46.606
l discovered l'm not the only woman
using my dog to meet men.

06:46.781 --> 06:51.989
Apparently, we also hunt in packs.
Come on, let's go get some water.

06:52.163 --> 06:54.072
Hey, Frasier,
l got a little favour to ask you.

06:54.248 --> 06:56.371
Duke and l are going on
a fishing trip next weekend.

06:56.542 --> 06:57.823
l need you to look after Eddie.

06:58.002 --> 06:59.746
Actually, l've got plans
next weekend, Dad.

06:59.921 --> 07:01.250
- Where are you going?
- Belize.

07:01.423 --> 07:04.093
Yeah, l saw that brochure
you had lying around.

07:04.259 --> 07:05.422
The fishing looks fantastic.

07:05.594 --> 07:08.512
Not to mention the sandy beaches
and lush grounds.

07:08.681 --> 07:11.885
Yes, Dad, l'm familiar with it.
That's where l'm taking Claire.

07:12.060 --> 07:14.267
And l'm going with Daphne. Well,

07:15.230 --> 07:17.852
if he's going, l'm going.

07:18.692 --> 07:19.772
Great.

07:20.361 --> 07:22.733
What the hell? The more the merrier.

