07:31.290 --> 07:34.457
Oh, by the way, thanks for driving me
and Claire to the airport.

07:34.627 --> 07:37.165
Frasier, please, are you kidding?

07:37.338 --> 07:41.633
Because of you,
my Kirby got a B in history. A B.

07:41.802 --> 07:43.795
Yes, it turned out well for both of us.

07:43.971 --> 07:47.590
For once, somebody else got the grade
and l got the girl.

07:50.019 --> 07:52.558
God, l hope Claire
is waiting outside.

07:52.731 --> 07:53.976
This traffic is terrible.

07:54.149 --> 07:55.264
[HORN HONKlNG]

07:56.443 --> 07:57.689
<i>[TYRES SCREECHlNG]</i>

08:06.538 --> 08:07.867
l didn't know you smoked.

08:08.040 --> 08:10.198
[COUGHlNG]
l don't.

08:10.376 --> 08:13.579
The way you're driving, l'm not
gonna die of natural causes anyway.

08:13.755 --> 08:15.629
Give me that.

08:16.508 --> 08:19.592
- Problem with my driving?
- No. No, it's fine.

08:19.761 --> 08:21.719
l just wish you'd pick a lane,
that's all.

08:21.889 --> 08:25.839
Pick, pick, pick.
You're certainly an expert at that.

08:26.018 --> 08:27.264
What is that supposed to mean?

08:27.437 --> 08:30.058
lt means that nothing
is ever good enough for you.

08:30.231 --> 08:31.560
You complain about everything.

08:32.484 --> 08:33.563
That is not true.

08:33.735 --> 08:36.357
Come on, Frasier.
l have been out with you.

08:36.530 --> 08:38.856
The wine has turned,
the silver has tarnished,

08:39.033 --> 08:41.524
the service is too slow,
the cheese is runny.

08:41.703 --> 08:44.621
Fine, it was Camembert.
lf anything, it wasn't runny enough.

08:44.790 --> 08:46.332
Yes, l may have exacting standards,

08:46.500 --> 08:48.908
but what you choose to characterise
as faultfinding,

08:49.086 --> 08:52.171
l think of as my steadfast
refusal to settle.

08:52.340 --> 08:56.005
Please, this Newport is more alive
with pleasure than you are.

08:57.971 --> 09:00.889
The truth is, Frasier,
you don't know how to be happy.

09:01.058 --> 09:04.178
- That is ridiculous.
- Admit it. You know l'm right.

09:04.478 --> 09:05.558
Wanna see me happy?

09:05.730 --> 09:08.731
You leave more than half a car length
between us and that Taurus.

09:08.900 --> 09:10.311
<i>[TYRES SCREECHlNG
THEN CAR CRASHES]</i>

09:17.159 --> 09:21.371
At least whoever gets my seat
on the plane will be happy.

09:23.834 --> 09:27.452
Dr. Crane? Dr. Crane?

09:27.630 --> 09:30.797
l understand your room
is not satisfactory.

09:30.967 --> 09:35.179
Yes, l had a reservation
for an ocean-view suite

09:35.347 --> 09:40.223
and instead, l got a single room
overlooking an abandoned bus.

09:40.394 --> 09:42.802
Now, please, sir,
you don't have to yell.

09:42.980 --> 09:44.060
l'm sorry.

09:44.232 --> 09:49.060
You see, my ears got clogged
somewhere above Xuahaca

09:49.696 --> 09:51.356
and they haven't popped yet.

09:51.531 --> 09:54.486
Now, if l could just get the room
that l reserved...

09:54.660 --> 09:57.032
l'm afraid we gave your room away.

09:57.205 --> 10:00.491
Check-in time is 3:00,
and we never heard from you.

10:00.959 --> 10:02.584
Let me see.

10:02.752 --> 10:04.626
At 3:00, my girlfriend and l

10:04.796 --> 10:09.293
had just disembarked in Punta Gorda
from our plane that was late

10:09.468 --> 10:13.052
because the pilot
had to dust some crops.

10:14.182 --> 10:19.343
l could have called
during my connecting tractor ride,

10:19.521 --> 10:24.398
but l had to find out which
of four airlines had lost my luggage.

10:24.569 --> 10:26.727
Not to mention--

10:27.197 --> 10:31.277
- My ears just popped.
- Congratulations, sir.

10:31.452 --> 10:34.369
l still want a better room.

10:39.711 --> 10:45.168
Frasier, this place is wonderful!
You should see the pool!

10:45.968 --> 10:47.795
lt's all right. My ears are better now.

10:47.970 --> 10:52.763
- Well, that's good news.
- Yes, we're on a roll.

10:52.934 --> 10:56.054
- Well, look who's here.
- Hello there.

10:56.229 --> 10:59.314
We thought you had decided
to hide in your hotel room all weekend.

10:59.483 --> 11:02.271
Well, actually, we just got here.
We missed our flight this morning.

11:02.445 --> 11:03.987
Oh, dear, what happened?

11:04.155 --> 11:06.444
Well, Lana happened.
We were on our way to the airport--

11:06.616 --> 11:08.574
Please, they don't need
to hear the whole story,

11:08.744 --> 11:10.902
and God knows l'm good for a while.

11:11.080 --> 11:13.785
- So who's up for a drink?
- You've got to try a Belize Bomber.

11:13.958 --> 11:15.785
Couple of those and you'll be flying.
Come on.

11:15.960 --> 11:19.211
Plus every one you kill,
they put a decal on your coconut.

11:19.381 --> 11:22.417
You go ahead, Claire.
l'm still working on our room.

11:22.593 --> 11:26.294
Frasier, this vacation
is going to do you good.

11:26.472 --> 11:27.801
This place is completely freeing.

11:27.974 --> 11:32.186
Would you believe that today
l dabbled in public nudity?

11:34.606 --> 11:37.442
Daphne and l found a secluded cove
on the beach.

11:37.609 --> 11:40.527
We shed our garments
and surrendered ourselves

11:40.696 --> 11:46.071
to the sand, the sea
and one rather curious grouper.

11:46.995 --> 11:50.329
Don't you have a diary?

11:50.499 --> 11:52.706
Well, look who finally got here.

11:52.877 --> 11:54.620
- Hi, Dad.
- Fras, how was your flight?

11:54.796 --> 11:58.046
Don't poke the bear, Dad.
And how was fishing?

11:58.216 --> 12:00.589
Duke and l caught the biggest marlin
you've ever seen.

12:00.761 --> 12:04.130
The swells were huge.
lt took us two hours to reel it in.

12:04.306 --> 12:05.386
Where's Duke?

12:05.558 --> 12:08.725
He's upstairs, sunburned,
heaving his guts out.

12:08.895 --> 12:10.971
You guys ought
to come out tomorrow.

12:11.147 --> 12:12.855
WOMAN:
Sir? Your table is ready.

12:13.024 --> 12:14.982
Thanks. Fras, why don't you
and Claire join us?

12:15.152 --> 12:17.441
No, thanks, Dad. We've reserved
a romantic table for two

12:17.613 --> 12:18.728
at the water's edge.

12:18.906 --> 12:20.187
Say no more.

12:21.367 --> 12:23.194
Well, l've gone on long enough
about fishing.

12:23.369 --> 12:24.698
What'd you guys do today?

12:24.871 --> 12:28.739
Oh, you know, took a swim,
got some sun.

12:29.209 --> 12:31.167
MARTlN: Just make sure
you keep your suits on.

12:31.337 --> 12:33.828
The skipper on the fishing boat
has a telephoto lens.

12:35.341 --> 12:38.960
He posts the photos in the bait shop
under ''Catch of the Day.''

12:40.722 --> 12:43.048
- Oh, look who decided to join us.
- Right.

12:43.225 --> 12:44.506
What happened to your table?

12:44.685 --> 12:47.355
We waited an eternity for our table,
but it never opened up.

12:47.522 --> 12:50.476
Frasier, this is fine.
Let's just turn our chairs around.

12:50.650 --> 12:52.608
Look, ocean view.

12:52.778 --> 12:54.272
MARTlN: Yeah.
FRASlER: All right.

12:54.446 --> 12:56.106
[ALL OOHlNG]

12:56.699 --> 12:57.979
Would you like a menu?

12:58.159 --> 13:00.033
You know what?
You have to have the John Dory.

13:00.203 --> 13:02.361
No, it can't be any better
than this halibut.

13:02.539 --> 13:05.990
Don't listen to them. These soft-shelled
crabs are melting in my mouth.

13:06.168 --> 13:09.371
Sorry, sir, but we're out of all three.

13:10.089 --> 13:12.758
Wonderful. Well, what fish
do you have?

13:12.925 --> 13:15.251
We make a decent swordfish.

13:16.262 --> 13:17.638
Decent.

13:17.806 --> 13:20.891
That's what l travelled
4000 miles for, decent.

13:21.060 --> 13:22.803
You know, you should put that
on your menu.

13:22.978 --> 13:26.348
- Home of the decent--
CLAlRE: l'll have the swordfish.

13:26.524 --> 13:29.478
Right. Swordfish is fine. Thank you.

13:31.113 --> 13:33.236
- Frasier, what's the matter?
- Didn't you hear?

13:33.407 --> 13:36.408
- They're out of everything l--
- Frasier, we've both had a long day,

13:36.577 --> 13:38.949
but we're here now. Why can't you
just make the most of it?

13:39.122 --> 13:40.236
[ALL CHATTERlNG
lN AGREEMENT]

13:40.415 --> 13:41.613
l'm sorry. l'm sorry.

13:41.791 --> 13:43.998
You know, you're right.
Okay, not another word.

13:45.087 --> 13:49.381
Well, as long as everyone's here,
l'd like to make a toast.

13:49.550 --> 13:50.961
Alrighty.

13:52.387 --> 13:54.629
That there's nothing
gives me greater joy

13:54.806 --> 13:57.476
than to see both my boys happy.

13:57.726 --> 13:58.924
[GRUNTlNG]

13:59.937 --> 14:02.891
- Mr. Crane, is something the matter?
- lt's reeling that fish in today.

14:03.065 --> 14:08.107
My arms are shot. l'll be all right.
Anyway, what l wanna say--

14:08.279 --> 14:09.442
[GRUNTS]

14:10.115 --> 14:13.318
Dad, don't be a hero.
Put down the coconut.

14:18.499 --> 14:24.336
Well, l just wanna say that l'm not
the only fisherman in the family.

14:24.506 --> 14:26.416
ln fact, l'm not even the best one.

14:26.925 --> 14:31.505
One year ago, after seven years
of trying to get her to bite,

14:31.973 --> 14:33.800
Niles finally hooked Daphne.

14:33.975 --> 14:36.846
And l think we'd all agree
that she's quite a catch.

14:37.020 --> 14:40.306
NlLES: Hear, hear.
- Thank you.

14:43.069 --> 14:46.770
And, Claire, l just want you to know
how glad we are that you're here.

14:46.948 --> 14:48.193
That's right.

14:48.366 --> 14:51.118
l don't remember Frasier
being this happy in a long time.

14:51.286 --> 14:52.366
Thank you.

14:52.538 --> 14:55.029
Out of swordfish too?

14:55.207 --> 14:59.336
l'm sorry, sir.
May l suggest the pepper steak?

14:59.504 --> 15:01.046
Steak?

15:02.007 --> 15:06.835
That's what we should eat
at Belize's finest seafood restaurant?

15:07.012 --> 15:12.352
There's an ocean full of fresh fish
not 1 5 feet away,

15:13.353 --> 15:16.354
but why not try
a slab of artery-clogging,

15:16.523 --> 15:21.731
hormone-injected,
frozen red meat instead?

15:25.533 --> 15:29.282
- l'm sorry, Dad. Please continue.
- No, that's all right. l'm done.

15:29.454 --> 15:31.696
Actually, l think l am too.

15:31.874 --> 15:33.831
- Excuse me.
NlLES: Of course.

15:34.001 --> 15:35.626
Claire...

15:37.130 --> 15:38.873
Claire.

15:42.260 --> 15:45.381
You didn't tell me
you had steak here.

16:02.617 --> 16:04.325
Claire?

16:04.494 --> 16:06.368
CLAlRE:
Yes?

16:10.501 --> 16:12.493
Listen,

16:14.046 --> 16:16.834
l don't blame you
for wanting to leave,

16:17.926 --> 16:20.678
but before you go,

16:20.846 --> 16:26.517
l'd just like to say that l'm really sorry
for getting so upset.

16:27.436 --> 16:30.806
You see, it's just that ever since
l met you,

16:31.816 --> 16:37.238
l thought that you were
pretty much perfect for me,

16:38.449 --> 16:44.120
and l guess l just wanted our
first trip together to be perfect too.

16:45.123 --> 16:47.958
And l think it still can be.

16:48.126 --> 16:50.166
What can l say
to convince you to stay?

16:56.636 --> 16:59.174
l see l'm off to a pretty good start.

17:00.140 --> 17:04.221
Frasier, l wasn't going to leave.
l'm crazy about you.

17:04.395 --> 17:06.886
l just started to feel
like you didn't wanna be here with me.

17:07.064 --> 17:10.397
Oh, gosh, nothing could be further
from the truth.

17:10.568 --> 17:12.645
l mean, this weekend
doesn't have to be perfect.

17:12.820 --> 17:14.565
Let's just try to have fun.

17:14.740 --> 17:15.819
- Fun?
- Yes.

17:15.991 --> 17:18.398
l can do that.

17:19.287 --> 17:22.573
Fun's been my nickname
since math camp.

17:24.250 --> 17:26.789
Math camp?

17:27.296 --> 17:30.297
You're just trying to get me into bed.

17:37.265 --> 17:42.426
l must say, this trip has certainly
taken a turn for the better.

17:46.317 --> 17:49.022
l'll tell you something else.

17:49.195 --> 17:51.769
l'm happy.

17:51.948 --> 17:55.115
Utterly and completely happy.

18:04.004 --> 18:08.713
l'm glad, Frasier. l'm happy too.

18:12.430 --> 18:16.131
CLAlRE: Frasier? Frasier?
- Hmm?

18:16.309 --> 18:18.101
- Frasier?
- Hmm?

18:18.270 --> 18:20.512
Are you okay?
You were talking in your sleep.

18:20.939 --> 18:25.436
Oh, yes. Yes, l'm okay. l'm fine.

18:25.611 --> 18:27.521
Go back to sleep.

18:49.180 --> 18:51.256
Hi, it's me, Frasier.

18:51.432 --> 18:54.967
Listen, l'm aware of the time.
lt's just that...

18:55.145 --> 18:57.470
You're the last person on earth
l thought l'd be calling,

18:57.647 --> 19:00.353
but l had this dream,
and l had to talk to you about it.

19:00.526 --> 19:03.017
LlLlTH:
Oh, God.

19:03.195 --> 19:07.739
l suppose you expect me to be
awake for this conversation, don't you?

19:07.909 --> 19:09.653
<i>FRASlER:
Okay, l'll be brief.</i>

19:09.828 --> 19:12.995
<i>lt's just that l'm on vacation
with my girlfriend, Claire,</i>

19:13.165 --> 19:15.870
a woman who by all conventional
measures is perfect for me,

19:16.043 --> 19:18.831
and yet l've just had
a vivid sexual dream

19:19.005 --> 19:23.252
about someone
who differs from her entirely.

19:24.761 --> 19:26.553
A man?

19:29.767 --> 19:31.345
Not that different.

19:32.520 --> 19:36.269
<i>- Someone you've slept with?
FRASlER: Well, yes.</i>

19:36.441 --> 19:38.399
But it didn't work out. You see, we--

19:38.569 --> 19:41.523
l worshipped her for years,
and then we had a parting of the ways

19:41.697 --> 19:44.402
because it turned out
that she was just unpleasant

19:44.575 --> 19:47.612
and confrontational, self-centred.

19:47.787 --> 19:51.620
Frasier, if you're dreaming about me,
just say it.

19:51.792 --> 19:54.996
No, Lilith, it's not you.

19:55.171 --> 19:56.879
lt's a woman named Lana.

19:57.048 --> 20:00.548
Well, it seems like
a textbook symbol dream.

20:00.719 --> 20:02.094
Why are you calling me?

20:02.846 --> 20:05.254
Well, because you know me
better than anybody else,

20:05.432 --> 20:08.469
and you're a terrific psychiatrist.

20:09.854 --> 20:11.017
Thank you.

20:11.481 --> 20:12.596
So, what do you think?

20:14.276 --> 20:19.353
As a working hypothesis,
l'd say you have the hots for Lana.

20:19.532 --> 20:21.821
<i>FRASlER: No, you see, maybe
l'm not making myself clear.</i>

20:21.993 --> 20:23.985
You see,
the woman irritates me no end.

20:24.162 --> 20:27.863
She's antagonistic
and opinionated, critical--

20:28.041 --> 20:31.624
So l see. What you're saying is that
unlike most women you've dated,

20:31.795 --> 20:32.994
she challenges you.

20:34.256 --> 20:39.002
Maybe so, but that's not the point.
You see, Claire is perfect for me.

20:39.679 --> 20:41.423
All right.

20:41.598 --> 20:45.548
Why does this dream
about Lana upset you?

20:46.937 --> 20:48.183
l don't know.

20:48.981 --> 20:50.725
Are you sure?

20:52.068 --> 20:53.860
Lilith,

20:54.780 --> 20:56.903
do you think l know
how to be happy?

20:59.618 --> 21:04.080
Of course you do.
You just like a challenge.

21:04.249 --> 21:06.822
You've never been one
to take the easy road.

21:07.002 --> 21:11.878
Well, it seems l've skidded right off
the road this time and into a ditch.

21:12.049 --> 21:13.378
A deep one.

21:13.801 --> 21:18.345
Well, you could try
to throw it in reverse

21:18.515 --> 21:20.721
and spin your wheels for a while.

21:20.892 --> 21:25.472
Or you could get out into the ditch
and get yourself a little dirty.

21:25.648 --> 21:27.771
l see.

21:27.942 --> 21:30.231
Lana's the ditch, right?

21:33.573 --> 21:35.317
lt's your metaphor.

21:37.077 --> 21:40.447
Well, l guess
l've got some thinking to do.

21:40.623 --> 21:42.201
Thanks for talking, Lilith.

21:43.042 --> 21:45.035
Any time.

21:45.629 --> 21:47.123
l love you, Frasier.

21:49.800 --> 21:51.757
l love you too.

